==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cellophane
<hw>cellophane</hw> <pr>(s⟦ecr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*f⟦amac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a transparent paper-like product made of regenerated cellulose,
produced in sheets and rolls, which is impervious to moisture and germs,
and which is used to wrap candy, cigarettes, and a wide variety of other
products for distribution and retail sale; <as>as, a pack of cigarettes
in a <ex>cellophane</ex> wrapper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cellular</ent>⟦br⟧
